texts.text: Gah!
Phew... Everyone okay?
No problem! We're good.
We're surrounded. I hope you're joking.
What's wrong? I've still got plenty left in me.
Let's do 100 more.
I need a break...
You're like a crazy fitness trainer...
Haha! That's the spirit, newbie!
What, already?
But there's no end in sight, yo.
Let's bust out through a weak spot in their defenses.
There's no need.
Stay still.
>Suddenly, drops of pure light start to rain down and barrage the demons!
*Scream*
*Groan*
>The barrage of light clears away the surrounding demons.
>The remaining corpses glisten with the light that fell from above...
Holy crap...
Phew. That was somethin'. But who...
Humans... What are humans doing in such a place?
Is there something afoot...?
Again, a disembodied voice...!!
Ah, my apologies. I will show myself.
>The blinding rays of light begin to distort and a being comes into view!
Now I should be visible to you...
Stay frosty, yo. We still don't know if it's friendly or hostile.
I am Marici. I have no quarrel with your kind.
At least, for now.
For now...
Just who are you?
No humans have been in this labyrinth until now.
I wish to know why you've suddenly appeared...
Right... We'll explain.
I understand...
You possess the means to fight against demons.
I assumed you were simply being assailed by those creatures.
But you've come here with something in mind.
I'm still surprised that you have such powers though.
Well, we'd be hard-pressed to say that it's our power alone.
Even this app for summoning demons isn't actually manmade.
But I am not mistaken?
The sun in your world is in the same state as the one here.
Yes, you're not mistaken.
It's missing the exact same parts as the one here.
Oh... I see...
You see...? What do you mean by that?
About this world, that sun...
I'm also yet to gather everything. My investigation still continues.
We'd like to know what you've learned if you don't mind us asking.
We need as much information as we can get too, yo.
I understand... I'd like to know what you've learned as well.
I shall oblige if you think it will help.
Great. First, what's with that sun?
You're not mistaken by calling it the sun.
However, the power of the sun god does not emanate from it.
It is some sort of imitation not blessed by the sun god.
Then it's completely separate from our sun?
No. There has and will always be only one sun.
It too is the very sun that graces your world with its brilliance.
Huh...?
Umm...?
I don't get it...
It's a fake...
In order to understand further, you must know about the master of this place.
The harbinger of the end... Tzitzimitl.
Tzitzimitl... The mastermind behind all this.
She ushers forth the end of days by descending upon your world.
The sun god has thus far made sure such a thing never came to fruition.
For eons, hundreds, if not thousands of years, she has battled against the sun.
She is an evil being that relentlessly pursues her goal by attacking the sun.
...!! No way.
S-Shionyan... Was that a lightbulb...?
This is only speculative, but...
Okay? That sun and our sun are one in the same.
Or rather, opposite sides of the same coin.
O-Oh...
Tzitzimitl wants to descend so she can destroy the world...
But the sun god prevented that from happening.
Her powers were negated up until now,
and she couldn't accomplish her goal with the sun god in her way.
But this sun isn't protected by the sun god.
Which means Tzitzimitl can't be stopped.
Yo, then she'll succeed...!
Well, yeah.
But that sun and our sun are two sides of the same coin.
So you know what that means?
Whoa, wait... Then our sun's in danger too?!
This is all if what Marici is saying is actually true.
So, did I miss anything?
No. Your conclusion is no different from mine. She... Tzitzimitl...
plans to consume the sun in this manner.
If she succeeds... Your sun will also be destroyed.
Her power of darkness will overwhelm it entirely.
When that happens, there will be nothing to stop her from descending.
And bring forth the end of the world...
The sun here cannot be protected by the sun god. But I can.
These attacks on the sun cannot go unchecked. I must go and stop her.
Aight...
Based on your story, this is our business now too.
Yes. We know what to do.
We're gonna help stop Tzitzimitl, yo!
Wait... But...!
I do not doubt that you have to means to fight against demons.
However, this is one that can destroy the world...
There is no reason to think that humans could possibly...
Well, you say that. But the world's going to end if we do nothing.
We won't just sit by suck our thumbs while we wait for it to happen.
But...
All good. We'll make sure not to get in your way.
Think of it as havin' more tools to find Tzitzimitl.
...I understand.
In the face of a powerful demon, I can only pray and wish for your luck in battle.
